TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(5,50,1);
$b = random(3,6,1);
$c = $b - 1;
$d = random(1,11,1);
$power = $a + 1;
$coeff1 = 1 / $power;
$coeff2 = 1 / $b;
$funct = "(1/$power) * (1/$b) * (x^$b - $d)^$power";

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

Evaluate the integral
\[ \int x^$c (x^$b - $d)^{$a} dx ,  \]
by making the substitution \( u = x^$b -$d \).
$BR $BR \{ans_rule(30) \}
$BR $BR 
NOTE: Your answer should be in terms of \(x\) and not \(u\).
EOT

$ans = $funct;
ANS(fun_cmp($ans, mode=>"antider"));

